Robust z-score was calculated for both normalized signal and relative infection index. First, median absolute deviation (MAD [34]) was calculated as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \mathrm{MAD}=1.4826\times \mathrm{median}\left(\left|{\mathrm{x}}_{\mathrm{ij}}-\mathrm{median}\left(\mathrm{x}\right)\right|\right), $$\end{document}MAD=1.4826×medianxij−medianx,and then the robust z-score was calculated for each siRNA as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \mathrm{robust}\ \mathrm{z}\hbox{-} \mathrm{score}=\left({\mathrm{x}}_{\mathrm{ij}}\hbox{-} \mathrm{median}\left(\mathrm{x}\right)\right)/\mathrm{MAD}, $$\end{document}robustz‐score=xij‐medianx/MAD,where x represents the set of all the normalized signals or the relative infection indexes of the samples and xij indicates the value for a particular well at row i and column j. The constant 1.4826 is used to make MAD comparable to standard deviation.
